How to Train Your Dragon is an animated adventure film set in a Viking village called Berk, where dragons and humans are in constant conflict. The story follows a young Viking named Hiccup, who feels out of place in his warrior society. When he unexpectedly befriends a dragon named Toothless, Hiccup learns that not all dragons are dangerous. Through their bond, Hiccup challenges the long-held beliefs of his village, discovering that understanding and compassion are the keys to overcoming fear and prejudice. The film is a heartwarming tale of friendship, personal growth, and the courage to defy expectations.

The flashed face distortion effect, occurs when two faces are rapidly alternated while fixating on a central point. Instead of seeing normal faces, the brain exaggerates differences, making them appear distorted. This happens due to adaptive face perception, where the brain enhances contrasts to distinguish features more effectively. The result is a surreal and unsettling transformation of otherwise ordinary faces.
